text: Bazoches-et-Saint-Thibaut is a commune. It is in Hauts-de-France in the Aisne department in north France. It was created on 1 January 2022 and consists of the former communes of Bazoches-sur-Vesles (the seat) and Saint-Thibaut. == References == Category:2022 establishments in France Category:Communes in Aisne
title: Bazoches-et-Saint-Thibaut
